A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Shelly-Ann Simpson on Women Veterans Appreciation Day
2 at the Capitol; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Shelly-Ann Simpson serves as the Executive Director for Field Operations and
4 Appeals for the Georgia Department of Veterans Service, the state agency created for the
5 purpose of advising and assisting veterans and their families through the complex process
6 of receiving benefits from the United States Department of Veterans Affairs; and
7 WHEREAS, appointed in June 2022, she leads over 75 percent of the department’s
8 workforce as they assist veterans with navigating the VA Claims and Appeals process; and
9 WHEREAS, she joined the United States Army Reserves in 1994, and was deployed as part
10 of NATO’s peace keeping mission in Bosnia in support of Operation Joint Endeavor/Joint
11 Guard in 1997, for which she earned a NATO medal; and
12 WHEREAS, she has served as the Department’s Women Veterans’ coordinator and the
13 Department Service Officer for the American Legion and is a tireless advocate for veterans
14 in the state of Georgia; and
